FBIS4-41925 "drsov125_g_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 25 Jun 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Poll: Support for Merger, Opposition to Sovereignty Loss Poll: Support for Merger, Opposition to Sovereignty Loss WS2906084694 Minsk SEM DNEY in Russian 25 Jun 94 p 2 WS2906084694 Minsk SEM DNEY Russian BFN [Report by Nikolay Levchuk: "Sovereignty, Anyway!"] [Text] According to a poll conducted by the "West-East" Strategic Initiatives Center, 76.4 percent of the Belarusian people support the unification of the Belarusian and Russian monetary systems. If the unification results in a ceding of powers to the Russian Government or Central Bank, the move will be supported by 39.6 percent of society. If the unification results in a loss of Belarusian sovereignty, only 24.5 will support this initiative.
